Response ID: resp_597
Response Text: One of the most impactful organizations for the visual arts in Austin over the past 20 years was Big Medium. The fact that an organization that gave space for over 1000 artists each year lost their city funding is a testament to how poorly the city is supporting existing organizations. I don't believe historically the people who are in a position to be able to make decisions about where funding goes understands the landscape well enough to be able to do their job well. ACME could better support the arts by investing more of their time, or partnering with people who do invest their time in understanding the existing landscape. I've never seen anyone who works for the city and makes decisions about the future of Austin's art community at any events.

